name: Franklin Innovation Fund
longDescription: In pursuing its investment objective, the underlying fund utilizes fundamental, bottom-up research to seek companies meeting its criteria of maintainable growth driven by innovation, which are leaders in innovation, take advantage of new technologies, have superior management or benefit from new industry conditions in the dynamically changing global economy;  invests in equity securities that generally entitle the holder to participate in a company's general operating results, including common shares, convertible securities and warrants on securities; may hold up to 10 percent of its assets in convertible securities. Franklin Innovation Active ETF seeks to provide capital appreciation through exposure to equity securities of companies with maintainable innovationdriven growth prospects.
